In article <1993Mar23.170327.2611@vixvax.mgi.com>, cepek@vixvax.mgi.com writes:
> In article <1993Mar22.205432.24384@ulysses.att.com>,
> smb@research.att.com (Steven Bellovin) writes:
> > But for key generation -- last time I was in a hobby shop, I picked
> > up an 8-sided die.  Generates true-random keys for me, 3 bits a roll...
> 
> For the non-octal-heads, I'll recommend a 16-sider to generate one
> nibble per roll.  A permanent marker altering 10-16 to be A-F+0 also
> simplifies things a bit.  Available at a gaming store near you... 

I wanted one, of course, but couldn't find any.  Apart from the fact
that hex is easier to fit into a DES key than is octal, I get one more
bit per roll.  I thought of using a 20-sider, with 4 labeled ``roll
again'', but I decided that that lacked a certain elegance.
